00290 static PyObject *Buffer_new(PyTypeObject *UNUSED(type), PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
00291 {
00292     PyObject *length_ob = NULL, *init = NULL;
00293     Buffer *buffer;
00294     int dimensions[MAX_DIMENSIONS];
00295 
00296     int type;
00297     Py_ssize_t i, ndimensions = 0;
00298 
00299     if (kwds && PyDict_Size(kwds)) {
00300         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
00301                         "bgl.Buffer(): takes no keyword args");
00302         return NULL;
00303     }
00304 
00305     if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "iO|O: bgl.Buffer", &type, &length_ob, &init)) {
00306         return NULL;
00307     }
00308     if (!ELEM5(type, GL_BYTE, GL_SHORT, GL_INT, GL_FLOAT, GL_DOUBLE)) {
00309         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
00310                         "invalid first argument type, should be one of "
00311                         "GL_BYTE, GL_SHORT, GL_INT, GL_FLOAT or GL_DOUBLE");
00312         return NULL;
00313     }
00314 
00315     if (PyLong_Check(length_ob)) {
00316         ndimensions = 1;
00317         if (((dimensions[0] = PyLong_AsLong(length_ob)) < 1)) {
00318             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
00319                             "dimensions must be between 1 and "STRINGIFY(MAX_DIMENSIONS));
00320             return NULL;
00321         }
00322     }
00323     else if (PySequence_Check(length_ob)) {
00324         ndimensions = PySequence_Size(length_ob);
00325         if (ndimensions > MAX_DIMENSIONS) {
00326             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
00327                             "too many dimensions, max is "STRINGIFY(MAX_DIMENSIONS));
00328             return NULL;
00329         }
00330         else if (ndimensions < 1) {
00331             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
00332                             "sequence must have at least one dimension");
00333             return NULL;
00334         }
00335         for (i = 0; i < ndimensions; i++) {
00336             PyObject *ob = PySequence_GetItem(length_ob, i);
00337 
00338             if (!PyLong_Check(ob))
00339                 dimensions[i] = 1;
00340             else
00341                 dimensions[i] = PyLong_AsLong(ob);
00342             Py_DECREF(ob);
00343 
00344             if (dimensions[i] < 1) {
00345                 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
00346                                 "dimensions must be between 1 and "STRINGIFY(MAX_DIMENSIONS));
00347                 return NULL;
00348             }
00349         }
00350     }
00351     else {
00352         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
00353                      "invalid second argument argument expected a sequence "
00354                      "or an int, not a %.200s", Py_TYPE(length_ob)->tp_name);
00355         return NULL;
00356     }
00357 
00358     buffer = BGL_MakeBuffer(type, ndimensions, dimensions, NULL);
00359     if (init && ndimensions) {
00360         if (Buffer_ass_slice(buffer, 0, dimensions[0], init)) {
00361             Py_DECREF(buffer);
00362             return NULL;
00363         }
00364     }
00365 
00366     return (PyObject *)buffer;

00376 static PyObject *Buffer_item(Buffer *self, int i)
00377 {
00378     if (i >= self->dimensions[0] || i < 0) {
00379         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError, "array index out of range");
00380         return NULL;
00381     }
00382 
00383     if (self->ndimensions == 1) {
00384         switch (self->type) {
00385             case GL_BYTE:   return Py_BuildValue("b", self->buf.asbyte[i]);
00386             case GL_SHORT:  return Py_BuildValue("h", self->buf.asshort[i]);
00387             case GL_INT:    return Py_BuildValue("i", self->buf.asint[i]);
00388             case GL_FLOAT:  return PyFloat_FromDouble(self->buf.asfloat[i]);
00389             case GL_DOUBLE: return Py_BuildValue("d", self->buf.asdouble[i]);
00390         }
00391     }
00392     else {
00393         Buffer *newbuf;
00394         int j, length, size;
00395 
00396         length = 1;
00397         for (j = 1; j < self->ndimensions; j++) {
00398             length *= self->dimensions[j];
00399         }
00400         size = BGL_typeSize(self->type);
00401 
00402         newbuf = (Buffer *)PyObject_NEW(Buffer, &BGL_bufferType);
00403 
00404         Py_INCREF(self);
00405         newbuf->parent = (PyObject *)self;
00406 
00407         newbuf->ndimensions = self->ndimensions - 1;
00408         newbuf->type = self->type;
00409         newbuf->buf.asvoid = self->buf.asbyte + i * length * size;
00410         newbuf->dimensions = MEM_mallocN(newbuf->ndimensions * sizeof(int), "Buffer dimensions");
00411         memcpy(newbuf->dimensions, self->dimensions + 1, newbuf->ndimensions * sizeof(int));
00412 
00413         return (PyObject *)newbuf;
00414     }
00415 
00416     return NULL;
00417 }

00467 static int Buffer_ass_slice(Buffer *self, int begin, int end, PyObject *seq)
00468 {
00469     PyObject *item;
00470     int count, err = 0;
00471     
00472     if (begin < 0) begin = 0;
00473     if (end > self->dimensions[0]) end = self->dimensions[0];
00474     if (begin > end) begin = end;
00475     
00476     if (!PySequence_Check(seq)) {
00477         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
00478                      "buffer[:] = value, invalid assignment. "
00479                      "Expected a sequence, not an %.200s type",
00480                      Py_TYPE(seq)->tp_name);
00481         return -1;
00482     }
00483 
00484     /* re-use count var */
00485     if ((count = PySequence_Size(seq)) != (end - begin)) {
00486         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
00487                      "buffer[:] = value, size mismatch in assignment. "

00489         return -1;
00490     }
00491     
00492     for (count = begin; count < end; count++) {
00493         item = PySequence_GetItem(seq, count - begin);
00494         if (item) {
00495             err = Buffer_ass_item(self, count, item);
00496             Py_DECREF(item);
00497         }
00498         else {
00499             err = -1;
00500         }
00501         if (err) {

00508 static PyObject *Buffer_subscript(Buffer *self, PyObject *item)
00509 {
00510     if (PyIndex_Check(item)) {
00511         Py_ssize_t i;
00512         i = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(item, PyExc_IndexError);
00513         if (i == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
00514             return NULL;
00515         if (i < 0)
00516             i += self->dimensions[0];
00517         return Buffer_item(self, i);
00518     }
00519     else if (PySlice_Check(item)) {
00520         Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slicelength;
00521 
00522         if (PySlice_GetIndicesEx((void *)item, self->dimensions[0], &start, &stop, &step, &slicelength) < 0)
00523             return NULL;
00524 
00525         if (slicelength <= 0) {
00526             return PyTuple_New(0);
00527         }
00528         else if (step == 1) {
00529             return Buffer_slice(self, start, stop);
00530         }
00531         else {
00532             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError,
00533                             "slice steps not supported with vectors");
00534             return NULL;
00535         }
00536     }
00537     else {
00538         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
00539                      "buffer indices must be integers, not %.200s",
00540                      Py_TYPE(item)->tp_name);
00541         return NULL;
00542     }
00543 }
